name: Tours at Climate Pledge Arena
description: Located at the base of the Space Needle in the Seattle Center Campus, Climate Pledge Arena is the world's most sustainable arena. On this 75-minute guided tour, you'll see the arena as well as areas usually kept 'behind the scenes' such as the locker rooms for both the Seattle Kracken and the Seattle Storm (subject to availability), the owners suite and more!

review.name: Love It!
review.reviewBody: Great experience! Well worth it. Access is awesome. Favorite: tunnel club, music act waiting area and recording studio.

review.name: Kraken game day tour that can't be beat !
review.reviewBody:
Javier is the BEST !!!!
Really, absolutely.
I've been on a lot of tours.
Thank you so much for this wonderful sharing of the beautiful Climate Pledge Area

review.name: Great and informative
review.reviewBody: Javier was a super engaging tour guide, we loved the tour - thank you for showing us around 💙✨ especially loved the music room, really cool

review.name: Highly recommend!!
review.reviewBody: Excellent tour with Theresa and Javier!!! Humorous, knowledgeable, considerate, and entertaining tour guides. Can’t go wrong, highly recommend!

review.name: Impressive and Wonderful Experience!
review.reviewBody: The tour of Climate Pledge Arena is wonderful. You get to see places the general public can't get into. It truly is an amazing building and impressive how they're climate neutral. This state of the art building has set impressive standards for arenas down the road. It was also extremely nice to get to go to the team store and shop with no one there. Our tour guides Collette and Heather were delightful and well informed. If they didn't know an answer, they called and asked to find out. I can't recommend this tour enough!!!

review.name: In the deep!
review.reviewBody: Javier was a great guide for a group of us visiting for a conference! The arena is so interesting and loved to see my new favorite hockey team's locker room!

review.name: Very Cool Tour
review.reviewBody: One of the better reviews of anywhere that I’ve seen in recent memory! Cool experience for fans of music, events, sports, technology, buildings, and sustainability.

review.name: ‘Kanucks’ visiting the Kraken House
review.reviewBody: Theresa gave us an excellent tour of the Climate Pledge Arena. Totally worthwhile to see behind the scenes.  Here from Canada. Make sure you check it out.

review.name: Feel like a VIP
review.reviewBody:
Want to see where the Sport players & Rockstars hang out?
You need to experience the behind the scenes tour of The Climate Pledge Arena with the friendly & passionate guides 🌟

review.name: Experience was well put together and very fulfilling
review.reviewBody: The Climate Pledge Tour was amazing! We explored and learned about the importance of climate change in science. It was very fulfilling. I would recommend many to take the tour.

itemListElement.name: Explore Rainier Retreat and Spa Adventure From Seattle

name: Explore Rainier Retreat and Spa Adventure From Seattle
description:
Join us for the "Fire & Ice: Rainier Retreat & Spa Adventure," an exclusive experience at Mount Rainier National Park. You’ll visit the park's most beautiful spots and relax at a mountain spa.

We’ll pick you up at the designated pickup point in Seattle and drive you to the park, where you’ll see stunning waterfalls like Narada Falls, Christine Falls, and Myrtle Falls. You’ll also have the opportunity to explore the Paradise area and stop at Reflection Lake. Afterward, we’ll head to an authentic Ukrainian village, where a firewood sauna, hot tub, and cold plunge await. You can choose to order food from their restaurant or bring your own.

review.name: Amazing Experience at Mount Rainier!
review.reviewBody:
The mix of adventure and relaxation was just right—hiking through stunning landscapes followed by a rejuvenating spa The group was fun and energetic, making the experience even more enjoyable.

I  recommend this tour to anyone looking for a unique way to explore Mount Rainier. It’s a perfect blend of adventure, relaxation, and unforgettable memories!

review.name: Epic Mount Rainier Adventure: Stunning Views, Karaoke Fun, and Relaxation at the Banya
review.reviewBody: Our trip to Mount Rainier was incredible! The hike offered breathtaking views that made every step worth it. The fun started early with a lively karaoke session in the van, setting the perfect tone for the day. After the hike, we relaxed at a Banya with delicious food—such a treat after an active day! It was the perfect blend of adventure, fun, and relaxation. Highly recommend this experience!

review.name: Not your average adventure
review.reviewBody:
Great trip to go on to meet people.
This included everything from transportation, cool hikes around Mt Rainier, and a stop for sauna/banya, food, and Cannibal Hot Tub. 
This is pretty much an all day trip but well worth it.

review.name: amazing weekend
review.reviewBody: I absolutely loved that getaway to Mount Rainier! We explored the Paradise area and spent time at a mountain spa—a perfect day enjoying the outdoors!

review.name: Pleasurable Experience for Any Level Nature Lovers
review.reviewBody: I have tremendously enjoyed the trip with WOW Adventures. I had opportunity to meet incredible people from my locality and we still maintain the connection. Katya, our trip guide, ensured that we encounter unforgettable adventures, stay safe and fed 😊. The day was full of joy… what can be better than meeting new people, going on the hike in the morning and finishing it off with time at sauna and hot tub?! I would highly recommend this group for any adventure… don’t think twice.

review.name: Best Trip at Mount Rainier
review.reviewBody: This was truly a WOW Mount Rainier adventure! Thank you for such a great trip and for organizing everything so excellently, plus the relaxing sauna closed the day perfectly. I enjoyed every moment spent in nature and breathtaking views. I highly recommend using Wow Adventure for your travels.

review.name: Weekend hike
review.reviewBody: I went on this trip with a group of strangers, but it was actually fun meeting new people! The park was beautiful, and the waterfalls were amazing. Highly recommended for anyone looking for a short getaway!

review.name: Must do Rainier experience!
review.reviewBody: The trip was amazing. The stops that were chosen were most mesmerizingly beautiful. The falls were at their peak and the mountain was full of fall colours. The cannibal hot bath, cold plunge and sauna was the perfect end to the day. Also, I went solo but had some really good conversations and so much fun. Totally recommend for a Rainier day out!

review.name: WOW - Must experience at least once
review.reviewBody: This adventure was so much more than I imagined! From beginning to the end it was just perfect. It was my first time trying such a tour and first time at Mount Rainier and I know this memory will last me a lifetime. Though I did not know many people in the group, by the end of the day we all felt like close friends. The hike to Mount Rainier was moderate but the views made it all worthwhile. The spa afterwards was just the perfect day to end the day. Alina, the organizer, is so thoughtful and makes sure everyone feels welcome and involved. I can’t wait for my next tours with WOW Adventures

review.name: Best Day Trip to Mount Rainier
review.reviewBody: This trip was awesome! We stopped at the most beautiful spots, and every moment felt so special. Absolutely stunning views at the trail in National Park! And the best part of the trip - the sauna, a delicious dinner, and meeting cool new people. Everything was super well-organized - great guide, comfy bus. Highly recommend this trip!

itemListElement.name: Go Fish Seattle and the PNW!

name: Go Fish Seattle and the PNW!
description:
Enjoy a memorable experience fishing with your professional guide as we target species found in the Puget Sound and beyond. We tailor the fishing to suit our guests from flounder and squid fishing to hard fighting Salmon and Halibut. We promise to work hard and ensure that your group has a safe and memorable time. 

For the month of December and January, we will be fishing for Pacific Market Squid along the scenic waterfront. Guests will be treated to a tour of Inner Elliot Bay with views of T-Mobile Park, Century Link field, Coleman Dock, The Great Wheel and views of the city skyline and Space Needle.

name: Winter Puget Sound Salmon Fishing
description: You will have the chance to see some of the best views in the PNW from the water. You will also be fishing for some of the best fish we have in our waters, the King Salmon. You may also get the chance to see whales and other marine life

review.name: Fun family fishing trip with Capt Matt Messing
review.reviewBody: My husband, mother and sister-in-law had a great time fishing with Capt Matt Messing. It was our first time fishing in the Puget Sound and did not know what to expect. We managed to catch a couple of nice legal King salmon and a few others that were carefully released. Matt is very knowledgeable, easy going, and even spoke few words in Japanese that made my mother happy. All in all, we had a great time and successful fishing (first time catching Kings). We hope to do this again in the Summer.

name: 9-course Progressive Dinner for groups of 6+
description:
The Pretty Fork is a dining experience for people in Seattle and the Pacific Northwest region where the restaurant selections and menus are tailored to each guest.

​Our belief is that disappointment is only derived through expectation. By keeping the location and menu a secret it allows you, our guest, to fully immerse yourself in the experience of dining. On our progressive dining experiences we visit 3 upscale full service restaurants all withing walking distance and dine on appetizer, entree and dessert within 2.5 to 3 hours. No tiny bites here, you'll eat enough for a full meal. We have a minimum group size of 6 people and beverage pairings are available upon request ($32/pp). 21+

We take care of everything. Our concierge works with you to define each dining experience. On the day of the event you show up, you group eats, and you leave. No confusing menus to pick from, no concerns about allergies, and no checks to split. In the end, you receive a delicious, effortless experience

itemListElement.name: Exclusive: Nine course, three-hour tasting menu tour

name: Exclusive: Nine course, three-hour tasting menu tour
description: We tailor our food, drink and culinary experiences to private group outings who are looking for an intimate, entertaining and flavorful Seattle experience. With thousands of successful group dining events under our belts, our custom events are the perfect way to get a taste of Seattle while enjoying valuable time spent with co-workers and colleagues.

name: Night Tour of Seattle
description: As the sun sets over the Olympic mountain range, take in Seattle’s most popular vista points with incredible views of the Emerald City skyline during this two-hour, live-guided tour. Hear wonderful stories and anecdotes about the Emerald City from your knowledgeable and entertaining narrator as you explore Seattle’s many interesting and diverse neighborhoods including popular points of interest from Alki Beach to the historic Seattle Waterfront.

review.name: Overraskende god aften tur.
review.reviewBody: Før vi skulle ud at spise aftensmad hoppede vi på denne nattur. Vi blev overrasket over hvor meget lokalt der var at se og høre om Seattle. Chaufføren, jeg tror han hed Les, fortalte mange oplysende historie om de lokale forhold fra før i tiden så vel som nu. Vi kom ud på Alki Beach som jeg slet ikke var klar over fandtes. Ligger over bugten overfor selve Seattle. Et fantastisk view af byen og et fantastisk Strandmiljø. Det var desværre stadig lyst helt til slutningen af turen men alligevel fantastisk. Vi kom rundt i mange lokale kvarterer. Virkelig en tur der er pengene værd.

review.name: Great Views from a Great Guide
review.reviewBody: Olivia was a great driver/guide. She used a blend of history, facts, and humor while maneuvering through Seattle Friday night traffic. This time of year it stays light so long there were no after-dark photos. But I got some great photos and I’m sure to use some in my annual calendar of travels

review.name: Terrible Experince
review.reviewBody: The tour was canceled and we were not notified or given any notice. Showed up to the tour and was told it was canceled.

review.name: Do no book!
review.reviewBody: Don’t waste an evening on this tour. Was not as advertised, not the double decker bus, definitely not for kids! Extremely hot and uncomfortable bus, and windows you can only see a bit out of on your side only. So disappointed!! And no ok is answering from customer service to help rectify the experience!

review.name: Seattle Night Tour 7pm
review.reviewBody: Our driver was friendly, knowledgeable & entertaining. His tailored tour was super awesome-it included great views/picture points. These were also from very different vantage points so that made it even more unique. He engaged everyone and was gracious and professional. I’d rebook any time and would choose this tour over the hop on, hop off ANYDAY

review.name: Affordable and easy tour of the city
review.reviewBody: This was an opportunity for us to see parts of the city we wouldn’t have seen otherwise since we spent the majority of our time downtown and walking between Pike Market and Pioneer Square. There were a number of places we wanted to see and this helped check a lot of them off the list.

name: Seattle's Electric City Bike Tour
description:
Make sure to bring your camera on this bike ride. You will have a state of the art Rad Power Electric Bike on this 14 mile 2.5 hour bike tour. After gearing up we voyage in style on the Elliot Bay bike trail on our way to Seattle Center. Then your guide will navigate you through a network of bike lanes through with many changing landscapes on our way through: 
South lk Union, Fremont, and the University of Washington. At UW we bike across the university bridge making our way to the bustling hipster neighborhood of Cap Hill where we link up to downtown.
Most of the tour in on protected bike lanes.
Must be 13-years-old and 5’0 to ride the Rad Power Electric Bike. 

Rider Experience: - Medium difficulty . If you have not been on a bicycle in some time you should practice beforehand.

review.name: Great WayTo See Seattle!
review.reviewBody:
Had such a blast touring several cool neighborhoods and places with Monty on RAD-brand electric bikes. Never operated an electric bike before but if you know how to ride a conventional bike and you can flip a couple of levers to change gears, use the throttle and hand brakes, it’s a breeze!

Speaking of breezes, we had great, sunny weather so the mountain (Ranier) was out/clearly visible. We started in downtown near the water, headed over to the houseboats (passed by the Sleepless in Seattle one), next over to the Freemont Bridge, past Troll Street, toured Gasworks Park, a cool nearby neighborhood, St. Mark’s Episcopal Church, Capitol Hill and back through downtown to complete our approximate 14 mile, 3-hour tour.

Monty gave great bike instructions, helpful city, neighborhood and historical information - and led us on and off the many bike lanes and streets effortlessly and safely.

Such a great way to see Seattle and bond with family and friends!

Book it!

review.name: Great ride!
review.reviewBody: This was a fantastic excursion with Monte as our expert guide! We enjoyed seeing discovery Park, and an area of Seattle that we would not have normally seen. Neither of us had ridden an electric bike before, but Monte was very patient and clear in his directions. Once we got going, it was no problem at all. Would definitely recommend this activity!

review.name: Fun electric bike tour
review.reviewBody: Monty was an excellent tour guide, the ride was fantastic, the bikes are amazing and I rate this 100% perfect way to see nature and Seattle.

review.name: Great Bikes Great Guide
review.reviewBody: After doing the city bike tour and learning about e bike we decided to try the Rad Power E bikes, We had a lot of fun with guide on this tour. Most of the tour was in a very beautiful neighborhood. It was a very casual easy paced ride. If you want to try out an e bike you found the tour.

review.name: Seattle electric bikes
review.reviewBody: This was a super fun and different tour experience that we all really enjoyed. The bikes were a little intimidating at first but once we got them figured out, which did not take long, it was a thrilling new take on a regular bike ride. The tour gave us great views of the Seattle sky line and took us through several interesting seattle neighborhoods. Riding for fifteen miles never felt so stinking easy!

itemListElement.name: Pacific Northwest-Style Dinner and Pairing in Seattle

name: Pacific Northwest-Style Dinner and Pairing in Seattle
description:
Get a taste of the Pacific Northwest in Seattle. Join Host Casey, whose cooking style is embedded in flavor, experimentation, and a full stomach, for a dinner experience that is one to remember. At his dinner, you'll see how he transforms locally-sourced ingredients into traditional dishes and be surrounded by new friends along the way.

• A Pacific Northwest-style dinner for 4-6 guests
• Eat fresh ingredients from local providers alongside thoughtfully paired, fermented beers and wines
• Witness Host Casey placing his dinner's finishing touches over the kitchen island
• Enjoy your meal at a long, oak table, or on summer days, on the back porch overlooking Seattle
• Guests are welcome to bring their favorite beverage of choice to dinner

name: Georgetown Brewery Tour
description:
Tour includes Lowercase Brewing, Jellyfish Brewing company and Elysian Brewing Taproom.

Founded in 1851 Georgetown is arguably Seattle’s oldest neighborhood. By the 1880’s it became the sixth largest beer producing district in the world and the center of Seattle’s early brewing industry. Now, with many of its 19th Century buildings still intact, Georgetown has experienced a revival as a hip neighborhood in a city of hipsters. Georgetown is now an important hub in the Northwest’s craft brewing community and a pretty cool place to have a beer.

At each brewery our Cicerone certified Beer Guide will lead a guided tasting of four, 4-once beers, for a total of 12 different beers. This is about 3 pints of beer. 

* 3/4 of a mile, 1,500 steps
* Each guide a certified cicerone
* 12 different 4 oz beers
* Free 4-oz souvenir tasting glass
* Free souvenir Bottle Key-Chain opener
* Beer & Food Pairing Guide

review.name: “ALE YEAH”!!
review.reviewBody: Tim’s “tour de pour” is Seattle at its “Hoppiest!” Tim’s tour will leave you full of knowledge, laughter…and beer “to boot!” Tim is a real beer expert “straight from the tap!” So use your “head!” Don’t be a “stick in the mug!!” Take “flight” with Tim and have a “barrel of laughs!!” 5 Star “Ex-BEER-ience!!”

review.name: Great tour!
review.reviewBody: Really fun tour. Tim was extremely knowledgeable about beer, funny, and a great teacher. We had a great time and learned so much! Highly recommend.

name: Emerald City Bicycle Tour
description: Join us on an Epic Bicycle Adventure experiencing the sights, sounds, and smells that makes Seattle a gem of a city.  After gearing up (see meet up location) we bicycle through Seattle’s Olympic Sculpture Park on our way to the heart of the city Seattle Center. Our bicycle guides navigate you through the hipster neighborhoods of Ballard, Fremont, South Lake Union, Seattle Center, and Queen Anne on an amazing interurban bicycle trail. Less than 2 miles is not on a protected bike trail, very safe. Must be at least 12-years-old and 5 feet tall. Daily 9:30am-12:30pm.

review.name: Splendid way to experience the beauty of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Fabulous bike tour around Seattle. Thank you Ivy for leading such a pleasant journey. Tour was well paced—not too slow, but not so fast there wasn’t time for photos or bathroom stops. Route was great. Bikes could be somewhat better. would not be a fun tour on a rainy or wet day bit really happy we did it. Look forward to trying the ebike version at some point

review.name: Seattle's Excellent ride and guide
review.reviewBody: This was an excellent way to learn about the different parts of the city and see the sights.  Our tour guide, Ike, was very knowledgeable and was able to adjust the needs of the tour to the group. She maintained an adequate pace while ensuring you had enough time at each stio in the tour and maintaining route safety. We look for to future trips to Seattle to explore the neighborhoods and events we learned about during our bike tour with Emerald City Bike Tours. Thank you for an amazing day!

review.name: Fantastic city exploration by bike
review.reviewBody: Had an awesome experience with Ike as our tour guide exploring the city.  She was aware of our safety at all times.,her enthusiasm and informations made the time fly.The city has wonderful bike lanes, which made the ride very comfortable. Good bikes, non electric, a few hills that the gears worked well to climb. Saw many of the highlights and out of way places.  So glad we took this tour, was the highlight of our time here. Thank you Ike, would take it again!!

review.name: Guided Tour of Seattle
review.reviewBody: Cycling tour of a large part of Seattle, taking you from the Olympic Sculptures to the Space Needle, through South Lake Union, to Queen Anne, Fremont and Ballard. The return trip takes you through Magnolia and along Elliots Bay. Guide Darrell was knowledgeable and informative, the cycling was reasonable for me but may be a stretch for some. There are a few hills and the bikes are not power assisted. I enjoyed the trip and it was a great way to see a lot of Seattle, although it would have been nice to allow a little more time to take pictures

review.name: Great way to see more of Seattle and n short space of time
review.reviewBody: Great bike tour, got to see a lot of the city across the morning. We love doing city bike tours because you get to see so much in the short space of time and hear good commentary. Seattle is a little hilly but all doable.

review.name: Seattle Bike Tour
review.reviewBody:
My partner and I went on this bike tour. It was perfect timing starting in the morning and going for about 3.5hrs. Our guide Tarae was down to earth, attentive, and kept the flow going. 

The bikes were lightweight and the trail lead us on a variety of paths. Each place was timed well for a break. I am a beginner and my partner is an intermediate rider, this tour was doable and enjoyable for both of us.

review.name: Don’t miss this tour!
review.reviewBody: What a fun bike tour! Our guide, Ike, was so entertaining, knowledgeable, and passionate about Seattle. She made us feel like her best friends! We saw so many interesting sites, never felt rushed, and the pacing was perfect. Highly recommended!!

review.name: Really Fun Day 👍
review.reviewBody:
I'm a lifelong resident of Seattle, but I quickly learned so much from Jonathon.  What a great guy, always smiling and enthusiastic.  As a fat middle aged guy, I wanted to do something fun and feel good about getting exercise at the same time.  Checked both boxes.  Have some great stories to tell at work on Monday and felt like I actually did something on my weekend.  I'm not a bike rider, but will go back just to see my new friend Jonathan again.  Thank you.
Matt Hillson.

review.name: Great way to experience Seattle
review.reviewBody: I really enjoyed this bike tour.  Our guide Monty was very knowledgeable about Seattle history and the wildlife we saw.   Guest safety really felt like a priority.  I appreciated the beautiful photos stops.

review.name: Jonathan a world class guide!
review.reviewBody: Jonathan was a fabulous guide. Shared some wonderful Seattle nuggets…even pointed out the way to Climate Pledge arena when I asked and confirmed my info that it’s a world class arena for hockey and concerts. Definitely recommend for anyone looking for an adventure. A real value!

itemListElement.name: One Way Scenic Seaplane transfer from Seattle to Vancouver

name: One Way Scenic Seaplane transfer from Seattle to Vancouver
description: Travel quickly, easily and conveniently on this international seaplane flight between Seattle, Washington and Vancouver, BC, saving hours in driving and traditional airport travel time. Border control will be available upon landing for efficient processing, allowing you to maximize your time across the border.

review.name: Water plane from Seattle to Vancouver
review.reviewBody: It’s an incredible adventure!! Exciting, seeing the extensive number of islands everywhere on the way to Vancouver was illustrating to say the least. If you have a chance to do it, don’t hesitate to go and enjoy. The best part was when we got to Vancouver; it was raining really hard but you fly so close to the skyscrapers that makes you feel you can touch them. Not to say, the takeoff from Seattle which is one of the most beautiful cities from the top I have ever enjoyed. Thanks to the pilot (can’t remember his name) for letting me ride alongside him and for been so incredibly skillful. Cheers to Kenmore Air

review.name: Dissatisfied
review.reviewBody: Had 3 flights cancelled in 2 Days.  They tried to refund through a future travel voucher.  No thank you.

itemListElement.name: 1-Day Snoqualmie Falls & Leavenworth German Town Guided tour from Seattle

name: 1-Day Snoqualmie Falls & Leavenworth German Town Guided tour from Seattle
description:
Have a relax day trip to the Leavenworth German Town and the Snoqualmie Falls departure from Seattle. 

Additional Notice:

1. The tour guide might change the duration for each stop depending on weather conditions or others.

2. The tickets fee should pay to the tour guide in cash and the tour guide will arrange activities admissions for the group. City Passes and Annual passes are not acceptable on our tours.

3. All meals and drinks during the trip are not included. The tour guide will provide eating suggestions.

name: Seattle Locks Cruise
description: Discover the best of Seattle on a scenic cruise through the heart of the city and experience the iconic Hiram M. Chittenden (Ballard) Locks, a ‘boat elevator’ connecting Puget Sound and Lake Washington Ship Canal. On the saltwater of Puget Sound, take in breathtaking views of the city skyline and majestic mountain ranges. Then, glide through the freshwater canal for a closer look at historic neighborhoods, commercial fishing vessels, floating homes, seaplanes, and more. Along the way, enjoy captivating stories of Seattle’s past and present from a live, local guide.

review.name: Sunny morning cruise!
review.reviewBody: Lars was our guide this morning. He grew up in the area and provided knowledgeable and interesting commentary. The crew were lovely.

review.name: Amazing cruise, 100% recommend to take this cruise.
review.reviewBody: Views were amazing and we took photos & videos. The guides were helpful and did an amazing introduction during the entire cruise.

review.name: Date adventure
review.reviewBody: It was a beautiful and entertaining cruise. We stayed downstairs most of the trip until we got to the Locks. Then went outside to watch the bridge fill and open the gate for us to pass.

review.name: Good trip.
review.reviewBody: Great tour guide, great experience. Hot beverages, easy boarding and ticketing. Would definitely recommend. Unique locks experience.

review.name: Great Cruise
review.reviewBody: We took this lock cruise on a recent visit to Seattle.  It was a great and informative cruise.  We really got to see how the locks work and there was a load of information given to us.  We were really glad we took this cruise.  At the end you could choose to take the bus or walk back.  We chose to walk back as it wasn't that far a walk back to the harbor area and it was a beautiful day.

review.name: Orca Surprise!
review.reviewBody: Ti actually experience the Locks was amazing! The narration was good and the wildlife viewing was wonderful! To see the orcas were an experience for these prairie people!!

review.name: Don’t miss
review.reviewBody:
We were lucky enough to have spectacular weather the day we took this cruise. The drew were very attentive and helpful. I particularly appreciated the PA system being so clear and the guides so animated and easy to listen to. We really learned a lot about the area.

I would recommend this cruise to any fist time visitor to Seattle.

review.name: Great Tour, Very Informative and Great Scenery
review.reviewBody: Glad we did this tour, we went from Lake Union to Pier 54 but you can do it the other way around.  There are other options but this was a great length at 2 hours and you go through the Ballard Lock which is made the same as the Panama Canal Locks.  You see around Lake Union, the floating houses, house boats, boat yards and the narration is very informative.  The other side of the locks you come out to the sea and then travel to Seattle Pier 54.

review.name: A Great Experience from Lake Union through the Locks
review.reviewBody: We had an amazing experience, and want to thank Captain Alex, Jackson, and Casey for going out of their way for our grandson Noah!

review.name: Fun relaxing informative tour!
review.reviewBody: The tour was great. Very relaxing, fun, informative, and enjoyable. Hesper, our tour guide, was spectacular. She knew so many things about the area and I learned so much. Captain Amy was fantastic too!

itemListElement.name: Mount St Helens Ape Cave Tour

name: Mount St Helens Ape Cave Tour
description: You'll feel the temperature change as you walk inside a dark cavern with flashlights and headlamps. It takes about 1.5 hours to walk down and back the mile long tunnel. You'll also stroll above ground on a boardwalk and see cement tree stumps! (from the lava flow).

name: Blake Island Excursions
description:
Cruise to nearby Blake Island – home to the famous Tillicum Longhouse – and experience Pacific Northwest adventure, culture and beauty with our 5-hour Blake Island Excursions. With two unique excursion options to choose from, there’s an adventure for everyone.

Explore the miles of beaches or trails, enjoy s’mores at a private fire table or relax in the backyard with a craft cocktail. Immerse yourself in the history and culture of the Coast Salish tribes through traditional storytelling, dance and food demonstrations.

Nestled between Bainbridge and Vashon Island, your Blake Island adventure is just a quick boat ride away!

All Excursions Include:

45-minute, fully-narrated boat ride to and from Blake Island
A mouth-water glimpse into the history of traditionally prepared steelhead
Buffet lunch featuring fire-roasted steelhead* and the famous Tillicum bread
Free time to enjoy the many island activities, explore the trails or relax

review.name: Misleading- bad customer service
review.reviewBody:
I had an old voucher and spoke to a manager back in the day and she told I could use the voucher in 2020. I went last week to their offices and spoke to their coordinator and he said, my voucher was still valid. 

A few days later the same person told me that they can’t accept my voucher because it’s expired. So they went from it’s still valid to it’s not longer valid. 

I would have used it before but Covid was thing... really unfortunate, them bouncing back and fourth, what horrible customer service. 

On top of that they never answer their phone hence I had to go in person and talk to someone. 

Also, the cruise is not worth $33 more like $20. 

Disappointing experience.

review.name: Relaxing & Fun
review.reviewBody: The cruise was wonderful! The observed the social distancing on the boat and at the restaurant on the island.  The food was absolutely delicious.  Can’t wait to try Argosy’s other cruises!

itemListElement.name: Seattle Premium 8-Hour Tour, City Highlights, Snoqualmie Falls & Wine Tasting

name: Seattle Premium 8-Hour Tour, City Highlights, Snoqualmie Falls & Wine Tasting
description:
If you have just 1 day to dedicate to seeing the absolute best that Seattle has to offer, this is the tour for you! We'll spend the morning exploring Seattle's top city highlights including the Space Needle, Pike Place Market, the Chihuly Glass Museum, Kerry Park and Lake Union. In the afternoon, we'll escape the city and you'll get an amazing taste of the spectacular scenery that surrounds Seattle. At the foot of the Cascade mountain range, we'll stop for lunch in a quaint historic railroad town, feel the mists from thundering Snoqualmie Falls, and then cruise along a country road to the heart of winery country, where adults will enjoy a complimentary full wine tasting flight! 

Your group of up to 14 can start and end their tour anywhere in the greater Seattle area! Cruise terminal, Seattle hotel, Sea-Tac airport--it doesn't matter. Loaded with too much baggage after your cruise? We've got space for 20 suitcases so you don't have to worry about it!
